description:
From Middle English bitreden, from Old English betredan, equivalent to be- +‎ tread.
Cognate with German betreten, Middle Low German betreden, Dutch betreden, Swedish beträda, Norwegian Bokmål betrede, betre and Danish betræde.

verbs.description: betread (third-person singular simple present betreads, present participle betreading, simple past betrod, past participle betrodden)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To tread over or walk upon.
